{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b80af57-10c1-4058-8a22-e7cafb3119ee","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why?**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints exactly which call must throw.\n- You can inspect the exception (message, inner exception, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b407d75a-bf17-42f8-9243-42a0e4a2871d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to search the codebase.","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"7C1D:21DC3D:2734684:2B82D3E:69F946AF"},"id":"a1205b01-1b6d-47e9-8d2c-a9dc2296d260","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:24:05.264Z","parentId":"7628214c-4920-4a81-a57f-d25b53d8de4b"}
